OL,3,C'I trusted partner' co-accused in baby
OL,4,Cmurder trial tells jury
OL,6,FHis body is apparently partially
OL,7,Fsuspended, his legs in a "frog-like"
OL,8,Fsetting and the child seemingly asleep
OL,9,For unconscious, in a "very unsafe" and
OL,10,F"dangerous" position.
OL,12,FThe defendant said he was cooking
OL,13,FSunday lunch and was called upstairs
OL,14,Fby Varley to see the child supposedly
OL,15,Fhaving fallen asleep again in an
OL,16,Funusual position.
OL,18,FHe said: "I remember seeing him over
OL,19,Fthe bars of the cot with his arms and
OL,20,Fsaying, 'Oh bloody heck, what's he
OL,21,Flike?'. And saying put him down."
OL,26,@oD@ZOUoD@dO]qD@VOUqD@bO]rD@AOUrD@KO]zD@
OL,26,AJOU}D@aO]
